quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  34,23,"And intercession cannot be of benefit before Him, except for oneto whom He has given permission{1}. Until, when fear has been dispelled{2}from their hearts, they say{3}, “What did your<sup>pl </sup>Lord say?” They say, “The truth; and He is the All-High, the Supreme.”",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Abu Amr, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…except for one who has been given permission.”],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Ibn Amer and Ya’qub read it as: “Until, when He has dispelled fear from their hearts, they say…”],footnotes:3:[They are either asking one another, or are being asked by the angels.]
  34,24,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Who provides for you<sup>pl </sup>from the heavens and the earth?” Say, “Allah—and indeed, either you or we are rightly guided or in evident misguidance.”"
  34,25,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “You<sup>pl </sup>will not be asked about the crimes we committed, nor will we be asked about what you do.”"
  34,26,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Our Lord will bring us together, then He will legislate{1}justly for us with the truth, for He is the Legislator{2}, the All-Knowing.”",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is a derivative of the word <i>fateh</i> which literally means open; some exegetes said that it means 'open a way for us to distinguish between good and evil', i.e. legislate for us a legislation.],footnotes:2:[Determiner of justice.]
  34,27,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Show me those you have attached to Him as associates. But no! Rather, He is Allah, the Almighty, the All-Wise.”"
  34,28,"And We have not sent you but to the whole of mankind, as a herald of glad tidings and a warner, but the majority of mankind does not know."
  34,29,"Thus they say, “When is this promise due, if you<sup>pl </sup>are truthful?”"
  34,30,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “You<sup>pl </sup>are promised a day which you can neither postpone for a while nor bring forward.”"
  34,31,"Those who denied said, “We will never believe in this Recital{1}nor in what came before it.” And if only you<sup>sg </sup>could see the unjust as they are brought to stand before their Lord, throwing back allegations at one another: those who had been deemed weak and oppressed say to the arrogant leaders, “Were it not for you<sup>pl </sup>, we would have been believers.”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is<i> ‘Qur’an’</i> which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
